<div id="review_3814042780" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3814042780" />
    <a title="Marcia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70266764-marcia"><img alt="Marcia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1592589911p2/70266764.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3814042780?book_show_action=true">Feb 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marcia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marcia" href="/user/show/70266764-marcia">Marcia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780571212156" href="/book/show/50148.Lizard">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3814042780" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12794489471195016082">Lizard is a collection of short stories on young adults and how they relate to their partners and to their parents. It particularly explores how young adults feel just before or after marriage, in a myriad of ways. The book is full of magical references and otherworld hallucinations, which help to illustrate what the new couples are experiencing. The other theme of the book - the relationship between young adults who have left home and how they relate to their parents - is colored with parental </span>
  <span id="freeText12794489471195016082" style="display:none">Lizard is a collection of short stories on young adults and how they relate to their partners and to their parents. It particularly explores how young adults feel just before or after marriage, in a myriad of ways. The book is full of magical references and otherworld hallucinations, which help to illustrate what the new couples are experiencing. The other theme of the book - the relationship between young adults who have left home and how they relate to their parents - is colored with parental and filial care and guilt. As the father from one of the stories admonishes his daughter, “Sometimes when people get married, old wounds from the past resurface.”<br />I thoroughly enjoyed this book - it is my third by Banana Yoshimoto - but some familiarity with Japanese literature or at least a disposition to pause and enjoy it is advisable for this book to fully touch you.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12794489471195016082" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

