  <span id="freeText14968301606573010358" style="display:none">I would probably say 3.5 to be more realistic about how I technically feel. If I had read this book several years ago I would have found it deeply prolific however now not so much. I did find the stories soft, soothing and lightly insightful. They feel pure and show a glimpse of a moment in time. We don’t get too attached and we hear a sliver. The thing in common with each is that they are all during a period of reflection or awakening. I think there is beauty in Lizard. It has left me with hope and new thoughts. With that said this isn’t a book that you need to read cover to cover and can be just a bit too light at times. It says the first story was posted in a subway, that’s how these read to me. It’s a collection of decent short stories. </span>
