<div id="review_624028026" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/624028026" />
    <a title="Jeridel Banks" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12011513-jeridel-banks"><img alt="Jeridel Banks" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442639796p2/12011513.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/624028026?book_show_action=true">May 24, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeridel Banks" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeridel Banks" href="/user/show/12011513-jeridel-banks">Jeridel Banks</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780571212156" href="/book/show/50148.Lizard">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer624028026" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9481692714704161481">Banana Yoshimoto&apos;s books are filled with surreal images, personal interactions, and drama contained in a shell of a book. <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50148.Lizard' title='Lizard by Banana Yoshimoto' rel='nofollow noopener'>Lizard</a>--a collection of short stories--is not this book. Unlike <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50144.Kitchen' title='Kitchen by Banana Yoshimoto' rel='nofollow noopener'>Kitchen</a>, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50158.N_P_' title='N.P. by Banana Yoshimoto' rel='nofollow noopener'>N.P.</a>, and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50143.Asleep' title='Asleep by Banana Yoshimoto' rel='nofollow noopener'>Asleep</a>, <i>Lizard</i> lacks character development, story development, and climax. In each story, Yoshimoto tells you the story rather than allowing you to experience the story. It feels closer to a teenager&apos;s journal: not believable and not memorable. <br/><br/>If you like Yoshimoto&apos;s books, you can skip <i>Lizard</i></span>
  <span id="freeText9481692714704161481" style="display:none">Banana Yoshimoto's books are filled with surreal images, personal interactions, and drama contained in a shell of a book. <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50148.Lizard" title="Lizard by Banana Yoshimoto" rel="nofollow noopener">Lizard</a>--a collection of short stories--is not this book. Unlike <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50144.Kitchen" title="Kitchen by Banana Yoshimoto" rel="nofollow noopener">Kitchen</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50158.N_P_" title="N.P. by Banana Yoshimoto" rel="nofollow noopener">N.P.</a>, and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50143.Asleep" title="Asleep by Banana Yoshimoto" rel="nofollow noopener">Asleep</a>, <i>Lizard</i> lacks character development, story development, and climax. In each story, Yoshimoto tells you the story rather than allowing you to experience the story. It feels closer to a teenager's journal: not believable and not memorable. <br /><br />If you like Yoshimoto's books, you can skip <i>Lizard</i>. You won't be missing anything. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9481692714704161481" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


